results.name: Decimal expansion of arccos(4/5).
comment: Given a square ABCD, there is one point M equidistant from A, B and the middle of CD. The measure of the angle BAM is arccos(4/5) (or arcsec(5/4)). This angle is the smallest angle of the well-known (3, 4, 5) Pythagorean triangle.

Also the polar angle phi of the viewing cone that cuts out exactly 10% of the celestial sphere; phi = arccos(1-2f), where f is the cut-out fraction of the full solid angle. - _Stanislav Sykora_, Feb 14 2016
link: Jean-François Alcover, Figure showing square ABCD and angle BAM
